         <notesStmt>
            <note>Damaged by damp.  Stained.  Wormed at ends.  Repaired and infilled, partially laminated. All edges guarded before rebinding.  Degrading ink.  Folios 100 and 101 mutilated. </note>
            <note>The leaf marked 1*** is a fragment cut out from folio 16 of the editio princeps of bYevamot (Venice, 1522). Some other leaves prefixed to the original manuscript contain poetical compositions, currently mostly illegible. </note>
